The '''41st Elite Corps''', later redesignated as the '''41st Stormtrooper Legion''', was a [[Legion/Legends|legion]] of [[Special forces/Legends|elite]] [[Cloning/Legends|clones]] in the [[Grand Army of the Republic/Legends|Grand Army of the Republic]], composed of many variants of [[Clone trooper/Legends|troopers]], including [[AT-RT driver]]s, [[Clone scout trooper/Legends|clone scout troopers]] and [[Biker Advanced Recon Commando/Legends|BARC troopers]]. Their legion color was alternately gray or marked with green camouflage. The 41st Elite was a division out of the [[9th Assault Corps/Legends|9th Assault Corps]], under command of [[Jedi General/Legends|Jedi General]] [[Luminara Unduli/Legends|Luminara Unduli]] and [[Clone Commander/Legends|Clone Commander]] [[Gree (clone trooper)/Legends|Gree]].

==History==
[[File:CmdrGree-TCWJA.png|thumb|left|200px|The 41st was led by [[Gree (clone trooper)/Legends|Clone Commander Gree]].]]
Though officially designated as the 41st Elite Corps,<ref name="Hasbro">{{HasbroCite|set=Star Wars: The Clone Wars (toy line)|packtype=2008 Basic Figure|pack=#26: Clone Trooper (41st Elite Corps)|altlink=https://www.rebelscum.com/TCW26clone41st.asp}} {{C|alternate: 2009 #04}}</ref> this battle group led by General Luminara Unduli and [[Clone Commander/Legends|Clone Commander]] [[Gree (clone trooper)/Legends|CC-1004]] was a [[Legion/Legends|legion]] of [[elite]] [[Cloning/Legends|clones]]<ref name="GGAR">{{InsiderCite|84|Guide to the Grand Army of the Republic}}</ref><ref name="Hasbro" /> from out of the [[9th Assault Corps/Legends|9th Assault Corps]]. The 41st Elite specialized in long patrols on alien planets, often operating in primitive and grueling conditions while forging alliances with indigenous populations.<ref name="GGAR" /> Seeing so many alien species even caused CC-1004 to become an expert on species and customs, taking on the name [[Gree/Legends|Gree]] to display his knowledge of obscure galactic species.<ref name="DB">{{DB|character|gree|Gree, Commander}}</ref>

The methodology of the 41st Elite caused the special unit to quickly become known as specialists in hostile terrain warfare, as well as alien recruitment and counter-insurgency experts.<ref name="GGAR" />

[[File:Unknown_Clone_Troopers_of_the_41th_Elite_Corps.png|thumb|left|300px|41st clone troopers arm wrestle]]
A year into the war, Gree and the 41st Elite participated in the [[Skirmish at Dinlo|Battle of Dinlo]], where they became pinned down by a large number of droid forces. [[Jedi General/Legends|Jedi General]] [[Etain Tur-Mukan|Tur-Mukan]] led a mission to evacuate the legion from [[Dinlo]]. The 41st Elite were then granted shore leave on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], partly as cover for [[Kal Skirata]]'s black ops missions, and partly as a morale booster.<ref name="RC: Triple Zero">''[[Republic Commando: Triple Zero]]''</ref>

[[File:Green_Company.png|thumb|right|250px|Members of Green Company defending the ''Tranquility'']]
One unit of the 41st Elite, [[Green Company/Legends|Green Company]], would see action on board the Republic Cruiser [[Tranquility/Legends|''Tranquility'']] when the cruiser came under attack from Separatist forces under the command of [[Asajj Ventress/Legends|Asajj Ventress]]. At that time, the ''Tranquility'' carried the Viceroy of the [[Trade Federation/Legends|Trade Federation]], [[Nute Gunray/Legends|Nute Gunray]], as prisoner on the ship. Ventress had been sent to either rescue Gunray or silence him, and the ensuing battle caused Green Company to lose eighteen men defending the cruiser.<ref name="TCW: Cloak of Darkness">{{TCW|Cloak of Darkness}}</ref>

Later, [[Green Company/Legends|Green Company]] saw action in the brutal [[Second Battle of Geonosis/Legends|retaking]] of the planet [[Geonosis/Legends|Geonosis]], after intelligence had revealed that [[Archduke/Legends|Archduke]] [[Poggle the Lesser/Legends|Poggle the Lesser]] had built a new [[Geonosis primary droid foundry/Legends|droid foundry]] there.<ref name="TCW: Landing at Point Rain">{{TCW|Landing at Point Rain}}</ref>

The 41st maintained a large armory with gray-marked [[Phase II clone trooper armor/Legends|Phase II]] and camouflaged scout armor for jungle duty. With [[AT-RT driver]]s,<ref name="SWPM1">{{SWPM|set=Order 66|cardname=41st Elite Corps AT-RT|link=http://www.swpocketmodels.com/images/shipo13c.jpg}}</ref> [[Clone scout trooper/Legends|clone scout troopers]] and [[Biker Advanced Recon Commando/Legends|BARC troopers]].<ref name="SWPM2">{{SWPM|set=Order 66|cardname=41st Elite Corps BARC Speeders|link=http://www.swpocketmodels.com/images/shipo02a.jpg}}</ref>

In [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]], the 41st Elite saw heavy action in the battle of Kashyyyk against the [[Separatist Droid Army/Legends|droid invasion force]] sent to seize the world. There, the [[Clone trooper/Legends|clone troopers]] of the 41st Elite fought alongside [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] warriors and a small clique of Jedi to a near standstill against the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy]]. While most of their men were transferred to Kashyyyk, a detachment of the 41st Elite was sent to assist in the [[Battle of Utapau/Legends|Battle of Utapau]].<ref name="Order 66: ARCN">''[[Order 66: A Republic Commando Novel]]''</ref>

When [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]] initiated [[Order 66/Legends|Order 66]], Commander Gree and his soldiers promptly turned on [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]], however Yoda sensed their intent and killed Gree and his fellow clone trooper and managed to escape with the help of [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]] and [[Tarfful/Legends|Tarfful]].<ref name="RotS">{{Film|III}}</ref>

===Vehicles===
[[File:41st_Elite_Corps.png|thumb|left|220px|Members of the 41st Elite on Coruscant.]]
The 41st was known to utilize [[All Terrain Recon Transport/Legends|AT-RT]] walkers,<ref name="SWPM1" /> [[BARC speeder/Legends|BARC speeders]],<ref name="SWPM2" /> and [[Infantry Support Platform/Legends|Infantry Support Platforms]] for anti-infantry and recon purposes, as well as [[All Terrain Attack Pod/Legends|AT-APs]], for artillery support, [[All Terrain Tactical Enforcer/Legends|AT-TEs]], and [[HAVw A6 Juggernaut/Legends|HAVw A6 Juggernauts]] as heavy missile platforms/troop transports.

